<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99249251813759></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99249251813759><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99249251813759>RE: About Agility</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99249251813759#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 14th 12:21 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.46]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>AGI over 100 definitely increases your AC, although I've never seen an exact formula for it.&nbsp;&nbsp;My current AGI is 106, and if I eat Hot-n-Spicy toelings (+2AGI, +2DEX stat food -- yes, I'm a master baker), my AGI goes up to 108 and my AC goes up one point.  However, the effect is NOT strong enough to make it worth loading AGI at the expense of STA/STR.  This is especially true given that AGI equipment is so darn easy to come by.<br><br>Getting ANY of the four key stats over 100 is a very good thing, for various reasons, and should be targeted.  The effect for each additional point thereafter, however, appears to be very marginal.  Given that STA is by far the hardest to get over 100 with gear alone, and that it has a direct HP effect, STA is preferred.  Given that STR is the 2nd hardest key stat to increase with gear, and that a monk is supposed to be the prime damage dealer in a group (barring a high level rogue), STR is also preferred.<br><br>Nothing really wrong with dumping everything into AGI -- you'll have a better natural AC than other monks, you'll just want to make some decisions on gear to compensate.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
