	   <tr><td colspan=2>You should, how ever, always be mindfull of the great differences between the human monk and his Iksar counterpart (begging the pardon of the gentlemen Keyeluke and Osano). Boosting STA is never as high a priority for someone with regenerate.<br><br>Also, in my opinion AGI for a monk is like WIS for a druid or INT for a Necro. It is the absolute prime stat and governs most of the things you would normally do as a monk. Although Iksar have a lower base STR than humans, the high DEX and AGI of the lizardmen more than make up for this, allowing you to hit more, if not quite as hard, and to get hit less and less severely - which also lowers the need for a high STA.<br><br>One further note on AGI-Equipment: Many many monks turn to serpentine bracers as their first (and brilliant) choice, with a set available for under 100pp, resulting in an whopping +18 AGI. This, I presume, is one of the reasons why some would say that AGI-equipment is easy to come by...BUT serpentine Bracers are PLATE-armor, so Iksar can't wear them, precluding them from at least ONE of the most readily available sources of extra AGI.<br><br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka, Xev<br>&nbsp;<br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679</a></td></tr>
