<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99237100785662></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99237100785662><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99237100785662>RE: new monk?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99237100785662#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>589 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 2:36 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.52]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've never been much of an advocate of starting over - invariably your early mistakes become irrelevant after a while.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you 'play through,' by your mid 20s you'll never know the difference.  However in your case, I'm tempted to tell you to go for restarting.  I remember my high teens being the toughest levels, and having no skill points to put into your most useful skills will make life that much more annoying.  You can practice your way around your 'misuse' of skill points, but I suspect you'll burn just as much time doing that as you would re-leveling up to 13.  And, you're far more likely to grow frustrated in the process.<br><br>You can restart or not - eventually you'll get to the same place.  Realize, though, that you'll have to re-learn your H2H, 1HB, 2HB, and dual wield - you can't just bypass levels 1-5 with experience points.  Monks are labor-intensive, as Osano has pointed out many times, and there really aren't too many shortcuts you can take.  Decide what you'd rather do, spend a lot of time mashing FD and ID when you get to 17-18, or start over and have to work up your basic fighting skills.  Have you been practicing up all your combat skills?  Have you developed any trade skills?  Have you developed any proficiency in Sneak or Sense Heading?  A yes to all these speaks against restarting.  A no argues in favor of restarting.<br><br>Hope this helps and let me know what you decide....<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
