	   <tr><td colspan=2>Easy.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bamboo bo stick.  8/20 weighs 1.0 lbs and should cost you less than 100pp.  Nice and fast, lets you get your 2HB up quickly.  Certainly not the weapon the adamantite is.<br><br>On the other hand, at your level I don't think you're facing too huge a penalty for carrying around the big stick.  Do an experiment - go to the bank, equip and unequip it, and see how much your AC changes.  It's a hell of a whupping stick for a lvl 11 and you're probably just fine eating the weight penalty for a few more levels at least.  You don't mention what your 1HB weapons are.  If you don't have any thing good, you might consider selling the Adamantite Bo, buying a Fighting Baton and Essence of Dol for maybe 700 pp, and spending the rest on some good AC gear - maybe some gem inlaid gauntlets, a foreman's tunic, or one of half a dozen other nice monk-friendly low to mid range items.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
