<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99232108769354></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99232108769354><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99232108769354>RE: New Monk</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99232108769354#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 12:44 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.56]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't worry about levels of special attacks too much at this point.&nbsp;&nbsp;The only ones that end up being important are Flying Kick, Dragon Punch / Tail Rake, and Eagle Strike.  Just take what you can get for natural increases when fighting, and use your best current (most recently obtained from guild) special attack.<br><br>If you're having trouble getting your 1HB or 2HB up it may be that you're fighting solo against high greens for experience.  A green /con MOB, even one that gives experience, has FAR FAR less of a chance to give you a weapon increase than a blue /con MOB.  Sometimes it seems more convenient to fight high greens as you tend to have less downtime, but you should really be looking for blues solo, or to be fighting even /cons to low red /cons in a group.  Go this route and you should have NO problem getting your skills up at lower levels.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
